[MK] case called at 2:34pm. 
Defendant George E Campbell in court, in custody, with Attorney Jonathan K McDonell.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
The Court finds that there is Chapter 950 compliance. 
Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " Guilty " entered; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts plea, finds Mr. Campbell guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court sentences Mr. Campbell to:
--serve 20 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Work-Release and Huber privileges; to commence forthwith
--0 days credit for time already served given
--pay costs of $243 plus $200 DNA surcharge= $443, to be paid in $50 per month installments commencing on 1/7/17 and on the 7th day of each month thereafter until paid in full; non-payment shall result in an 8 day jail term with work-release and Huber privileges, consecutive
The Court determines that there is already a DNA sample on file for Mr. Campbell. The Court does not order DNA sample provision in this case.
